Action items from the Cordel Service Desk and Processing Request Service Desk

Annual pay reviews

Job Description


Data Engineering at Nine empowers individuals to own delivery end-to-end, and explore how new data and the latest Data & AI technologies can improve workflows, and deliver greater value for our stakeholders.

We have a great opportunity for a Data Engineer to join our Commercial Growth Squad.Your role will be instrumental in building and sustaining Nine's competitive advantage through data, as you'll focus on the full development and maintenance lifecycle of innovative data products. This critical work directly empowers our business to create unique, actionable insights, which are essential for driving strategy and maximising our ad revenue.

What you’ll do:

Develop and maintain reliable data pipelines (ETL) to load and transform data from various sources into data warehouses.

Ensure pipelines are scalable and efficient, considering factors like data volume, velocity, and variety.

Implement data quality checks and validation processes to maintain accurate data.

Perform root cause analysis for incidents and implement corrective actions.

Contribute to the technical design and vision for the data platform.

Explore new AI technologies and methods to enhance value delivery across Data Engineering workflows.

Qualifications


What you’ll bring:

Strong programming ability in at least one language (e.g., Python).

Proficiency in SQL.

Data Modeling experience, including the application of abstract concepts in an enterprise environment.

Proven experience designing and building data pipelines, ETL processes, and managing data infrastructure.

Experience delivering workflow orchestration solutions and managing task dependencies using a tool like Apache Airflow.

 A strong analytical mindset, a passion for tackling complex technical challenges, and the ability to find creative solutions to issues.

Desirable:

A bachelor's or master's degree in Computer Science, Software/Data Engineering, Data Science, IT, or a related field.

Experience with Google Cloud Platform (GCP), AWS, or Azure, including their data storage, processing, and analytics services.

Familiarity with cloud deployment and test automation using a CI/CD solution (e.g., Cloud Build, Dagger, or Concourse).

Experience in deploying cloud infrastructure as code (IaC) using Terraform or similar tools.

Experience leveraging AI to deliver Data Engineering solutions.

Additional Information

At Nine, our flexible work options vary by role and team. Depending on the position, this may include flexible hours, hybrid work, or part-time arrangements. We welcome discussing your flexibility needs during the hiring process - just ask the Talent Acquisition team. 

Our employee benefits include:

18 weeks paid parental leave with no distinction between primary and secondary carers.
Access to 'Employee Exclusives' program - a way of getting closer to our incredible brands, offering unique experiences, behind-the-scenes access, and awesome perks.

Annual gift voucher for Stan subscription.

More info at Nine Careers.

Our Commitment to Diversity and Inclusion:

We're committed to a safe, respectful and inclusive Nine. From day one, you'll be encouraged to bring your whole self to work and will be supported to perform at your best.

We encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, people with disabilities, and of all ages, genders, nationalities, backgrounds and cultures as we recognise the importance and value of diverse perspectives. Should you require any adjustments to the recruitment process, please advise us when you apply.

Work rights: Please note to apply for this role you must already have the right to lawfully work and live in Australia.

Our office will be closed for the annual End-of-Year shutdown from December 22nd to January 2nd.
Applications will be reviewed upon our return from January 5th, 2026. Thank you in advance for your understanding while our Talent Acquisition team takes a break. We look forward to connecting with you in the New Year and wish you a safe and happy holiday.

Job description:

Join us as a Pioneer and Strategic Builder in AI Innovation!

Australian Unity is embarking on a major transformation, shifting from traditional automation toward an intelligent, AI-powered future. We're looking for a Senior AI Automation Engineer to help shape this next generation of automation: one where AI Agents, large language models (LLMs), and modern frameworks transform how we work and deliver value to our customers.

In this hands on and strategic role, you'll play a key part in modernising our automation ecosystem; maintaining and enhancing current platforms (Appian, UiPath, Power Automate) while designing and implementing cutting-edge, AI-driven automation ecosystem. You'll combine deep technical expertise with creative problem solving, using first principles thinking to challenge the status quo, simplify complexity, and drive enterprise-wide efficiency.

This is a unique opportunity to lead the transition from classical RPA to AI-centric automation, setting the foundation for an adaptive, scalable, and future-ready technology landscape.

What You'll Do

· Lead end-to-end automation delivery, from concept to deployment.

· Modernise existing Automation ecosystem while building the foundations for AI Agent driven automation.

· Design and implement next generation automation using Generative AI, MCP Servers, and agent frameworks, extending the boundaries of what automation can do.

· Define and embed best practice design patterns, reusable modules, and delivery frameworks that improve speed, scalability, and governance.

· Monitor and optimise automation performance and outcomes to ensure business impact and alignment with strategic goals.

· Maintain and enhance current automation pipelines (Appian, UiPath, Power Automate), ensuring stability as we evolve the stack.

· Collaborate across business and technology teams to translate complex problems into practical, measurable automation solutions.

· Mentor and guide junior and offshore engineers, fostering a culture of innovation and technical excellence.

· Stay ahead of emerging technologies in AI, automation, and machine learning and bring fresh ideas that keep us at the forefront of innovation.

About You

We are looking for an innovator who's curious, forward-thinking, and thrives on solving complex challenges. You will bring a mix of hands-on technical skill and architectural vision. You question legacy approaches, design from first principles, and are excited by the possibilities of AI and automation convergence.

We also value an entrepreneur's mindset - someone who can wear multiple hats, adapt fluidly to new challenges, and take on roles beyond coding to deliver meaningful business impact. Start-up or similar experience that demonstrates versatility, ownership, and comfort operating in a fast-changing environment - whether as a founder or an early employee - will be highly regarded.

You will have:

· Degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field 5+ years commercial experience with at least 2 years in a relevant technical or architect capacity

· Proven track record delivering complex AI/ML solutions

You'll have hands-on experience with:

· Generative AI & agentic frameworks (LangChain, LangGraph, AutoGen, MCP Servers, etc.)

· Proficiency in at least one programming language (preferably Python), with strong OOP and design-pattern skills, and the ability to deliver high-quality, well-tested code.

· Excellent problem-solving skills and ability to translate business needs into technical solutions.

· Deep technical / theoretical knowledge in at least one of the following sub-fields of AI: Machine Learning, Deep Learning, or Foundation Models

· Ability to collaborate with stakeholders and communicate technical concepts clearly · Technology/AI architecture, governance, responsible AI frameworks and scalability in enterprise environments

· Familiarity with RPA/BPA platforms such as UiPath, Appian, and Power Automate or strong willingness to learn.

What's on Offer:

You will enjoy a range of great employee benefits and rewards including:

· Competitive salary + bonus program

· Enjoy additional yearly Well-Being and Community leave days

· 14-week paid parental leave, with equal benefit for both parents

· Employee Referral Program

· Employee Assistance Program - support and assistance for you and your partner at those times in life when you need it most

· Maxxia Rewards - a great range of discounts and benefits at selected retail outlets, department stores, attractions, travel, cinemas, restaurants.

· Discounts across the Australian Unity business including Private Health Insurance, General Insurance + more!

· Available access to LinkedIn Learning courses through our great Learning platform.

For further benefits visit: https://www.australianunity.com.au/careers/culture

Australian Unity is an Equal Opportunity employer and we encourage applications from all members of the community, including people of Aboriginal and Torres strait Islander descent, culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds and, mature aged people.

Excellent problem-solving, communication, and stakeholder management skills.

Family owned since 1988, Thomas Foods International (TFI) is one of Australia's largest food businesses. With teams across Australia, the US, Canada, China, Japan & Europe. TFI is an organisation that truly embodies its values-driven philosophy & positive working culture. Now, is the perfect time to join this innovative, growing global business.

Discover an exciting career opportunity at our Stawell meat processing plant, your gateway to the stunning Grampians region. You'll work with a passionate and diverse team that's empowered to achieve big things and deliver at pace.

The Role

This is a chance to build a lasting career with a stable company that's investing in its future with significant site expansion and new technology. 

This pivotal role of a Controls and Automation Technician is responsible for designing, developing, & maintaining control systems and automation solutions across the site.  Working on projects involving the integration of hardware & software components to optimise operational efficiency, enhance safety, & improve productivity.

This role requires a strong understanding of electrical engineering principles, programming skills, and knowledge of control systems.

The Quality Ingredients for Success 

Just like our best cuts of meat, there are a few essential qualities that we need and look for in this role:

System Design & Development:

Cross-functional teams system requirements & specifications. Design & develop control systems & automation solutions platforms.

Recommend technologies & methodologies to create system for schematics, diagrams, & technical specifications.

Programming and Configuration::

Develop & implement control algorithms & (ladder) logic programming. Configure & program  (PLCs),  (DCS), (HMIs), & control devices.

Integrate the control system, sensors, actuators, & communication networks.  Conduct debugging of software system functionality.

System Integration and Commissioning:

Suppliers & contractors to integrate control systems into processes. Coordinate system installation, testing, & commissioning activities. 
 

System troubleshooting & resolve issues for performance or interface problems. Fine-tuning parameters, control strategies, & conducting system performance analysis.

Continuous Improvement:

Improve, enhance or modify existing control systems  requirements.  

Maintain system documentation & update, with the latest industry trends, standards, & technologies related to controls & automation. 

Collaboration and Communication:

Multidisciplinary teams, including Elect & Mech engineers, electrical & mechanical trades & software developers for troubleshooting & resolution of control system issues.

Experience & Qualifications

Bach degree in Elect Eng, Automatic Eng, or related field/in-depth industry experience.

Control systems theory, process control, & automation principles. Programming such as ladder logic, structured text, or function block diagram. Experience with PLCs, DCSs, HMIs, & from manufacturers.

Industrial communication protocols (OPC, Modbus, Ethernet/IP). Elect & Elect systems, including sensors, actuators, & motor control.

Read & interpret electrical schematics & technical drawings.  Problem-solving skills & the ability to analyse complex systems.

Communication & teamwork abilities. Strong attention to detail & a commitment to delivering high-quality work.

Knowledge of relevant safety regulations &standards in the industry.

3-5 years’ experience in a similar role 




Apply today to be part of this exciting opportunity!

Your next exciting career move awaits in Stawell! Here, you'll find the perfect blend of a fulfilling career and a relaxed country lifestyle with modern conveniences.
